        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32525",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "finfo works also in 5.2.4 without setting the magic constant.\n\nWhen you want to use a own magic file you must also set the related option. There is no way to detect which mime database you want to use when you don't set it and your php.ini does also not give a proper location.\n\nThis is not a ZF issue, this is just a mis-configuration of your php.ini file. See the ZF documentation for details.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-10T15:44:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-10T15:44:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32527",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dustins",
                        "name": "dustins",
                        "displayName": "Dustin Sweigart",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can I suggest the documentation be changed then? It isn't consistent with how the finfo constructor behaves...\n{quote}\nName of a magic database file, usually something like \/path\/to\/magic.mime. If not specified, the MAGIC environment variable is used. If this variable is not set either, \/usr\/share\/misc\/magic is used by default. A .mime and\/or .mgc suffix is added if needed.\n{quote}\n\nSurely it would be easy to assign the browser given mime type to $this->_type by default and then replace it if finfo is available and can be constructed or if mime_content_type() is available. This would create more consistency with finfo itself and allow more people to use it without making demands of their php.ini file that aren't actually a requirement (or mis-configuration) by finfo\/PHP.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dustins",
                        "name": "dustins",
                        "displayName": "Dustin Sweigart",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-10T16:36:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-10T16:36:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32529",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "How finfo behaves depends on your OS and your settings.\nWhen you have not configured finfo properly there is no way for ZF to use it.\n\nThe magic constant defines when the magic file can be found. There is no way to find this file automatically.\n\nStill, when you have problems with finfo you should first take a look into php's finfo manual page. ZF should not double php's manual on how extensions should be configured.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-11T08:21:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-11T08:21:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
